commit.message:
Introduce ASCII_OPTIONS; Use None for default options

Applying requested code-review changes
Fix pep8 violation
Consistently use unicode strings

Make tree print characters configurable; Introduce format_ascii_tree

Previously, the characters the tree used for printing the tree were hard-coded.
This is now configurable using an optional 'option' parameter passed into format_tree.

I also used this to introduce a 'format_ascii_tree' which uses only ASCII based
print characters.

Without this, sometimes Windows blows up (I'm not quite sure why) trying to
decode the UTF-8 as CP1252.
